HEADWORD: gumweed
<hw>gumweed</hw> <pos>n.</pos> <def>any of various Western American
plants of the genus <gen>Grindelia</gen> having resinous leaves and
stems formerly used medicinally; often poisonous to livestock.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> gum plant, tarweed, rosinweed, rosin-weed.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

